Veteran Ejike Asiegbu is mourning the death of his aged father. According to Asiegbu, the late Chief J.U Asiegbu died on January 15, 2022 at 105. “With gratitude to God for a life well spent, I wish to inform you of the transition of my dear father Engr. Chief, Sir J.U Asiegbu (Nna Oha) to eternal glory.   Joeboy hits 100 million streams on Boomplay     Bobrisky allegedly sets to wed ‘billionaire lover’     Social media reacts to Instagram celebrity Mompha N200m bail   “He was the oldest man in Umuihi Umuogba Ekeoba in Umuahia North Local Government Area of Abia state. “He passed on January 15, 2022. He was 100 years old plus. - Advertisement - “He is survived by wife, children, many children and grandchildren. “Funeral rites announcements would be made later. Please remember our family in your prayers.”